dataIdInfo.idPurp: The purpose of this layer is to assess urban tree canopy in Fairfax County, Virginia by Census Tract. The tree canopy percent is calculated by dividing the tree canopy area by the total area of the census tract minus the area within the census tract that is identified as water (Tree Canopy/(Total Area â€“ Water Area)).
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
This data represents detailed tree canopy cover in Fairfax County, Virginia. The data was derived from the 2021 Land Cover raster dataset which used remote sensing technologies on aerial imagery from the National Agriculture Imagery Program (NAIP), flown in 2021 and filtered by the tree attribute and converted to polygons. The land cover data was procured through a Tree Planting and Preservation Fund (TPPF) grant given by the County to Casey Trees. Casey Trees contracted with PlantIT Geo to perform the analysis. The data was then calculated to the Census Tract level to find the percent of tree canopy per land areas of each census tract minus the area that is identified as water.
